Deploying To Azure Container Registry

PHASE 1: DEPLOYING LOCALLY
STEP 1: Docker 
Ensure Docker is running on your local machine.
  - docker version (Else you might need to install it).
  - Once that is done, ensure docker is running.
  - docker ps (to view the images on your system).

STEP 2: Nginx Image
  - Pull an Nginx image from the dockerHub.
  - Run the image on your machine
  - docker run --name nginxnew -d -p 8080:80 nginx
  - docker ps (View the running image)
  - View the Nginx server in the browser. CONGRATS!!

STEP 3: Creating a Dockerfile
  - Navigate to the intended directory.
  - create a Dockefile, HTML file & notes.txt.
  - Dockerfile (Contents)
    -FROM nginx
    COPY ./index.html /usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
    EXPOSE 80
  - Build The Image
    - docker build -t jaynginx -f Dockerfile .
    - docker images:- to view the created image.
  - Run The Image
    - docker run --name jaynginxnew -d -p 8080:80 jaynginx
    - View in Browser

PHASE 2: DEPLOYING TO THE CLOUD

STEP 1: Deploying to Azure.
  - Log in to Azure Account.
    - az login (Log in Microsoft Account)
    - az resource list (to ensure the account has been logged into).
    
STEP 2: Create a Resource Group.
  - az group create --name jayrg --location uksouth (Resource Group - "jayrg")
  -  Deploy the resource group.
     - az acr create --resource-group dockerrg --name jaydockerdemo --sku Basic
     - *az acr create --resource-group jayrg --name jayacrdemo --sku Basic *
  -  Look for the loginServer credentials in the log.
  - Login into the Azure container registry.
    - az acr login --name jaydcokerdemo.azurecr.io

STEP 3: Pushing Image Into Container Registry.
  - Tag the Image
    - docker tag jaynginx jaydcokerdemo.azurecr.io/jaynginx
  - Push Image into registry
    - docker push jaydcokerdemo.azurecr.io/jaynginx
  - Head into Resource Groups
    - View Image.

STEP 4: Running Image In The Cloud.
  - Head To Azure Container Instances.
    - Create a Container instance
    - Select jayresourcegroup, select jaydcokerdemo as registry
    ** ENABLE ADMIN USER FOR REGISTRY TO ACCESS IMAGE DURING CONTAINER INSTANCE CREATION**
      - Go to jaydcokerdemo in resource groups and access keys to enable admin.
  - Continue to Building the Image.
STEP 5: View Page.
  - To View the Page, Copy the FDQN link and access it in the Browser.
  CONGRATULATIONS!!!!
